packs.staffComments: This pack is designed for players looking to improve their air dribble game. It consists of 15 shots where the ball is bounced off the ground once before the player goes for the air dribble. These shots require precise timing, control, and aerial skills. They are intended for players who are comfortable with advanced mechanics and are trying to perfect their offensive play at the highest level of play.
packs.name: 1 Bounce Air Dribble
packs.creator: Lazord
packs.notes:
Wait for the ball to bounce and take it on an air dribble. These shots simulate gamelike situations that present opportunities for controlled aerial plays.

At a basic level, you want to work on creating a soft first touch while maintaining control of your car to follow it up in the air. Once you're comfortable with this, it's important to make sure you're not just getting 2-3 touches and carrying it into net, but you should really try to match your speed and connect with the ball so that it isn't bouncing away from you.

A high quality attempt at each shot includes altering the trajectory of the initial touch in a way that could realistically get past a defender.

packs.staffComments: This pack will test your ability to control the ball while challenging you to make precise hits from the ceiling. Perfect for players looking to improve their defensive capabilities and add a new dimension to their gameplay.
packs.name: Ceiling Challenges
packs.creator: Wayprotein
packs.notes:
This pack is designed to get you familiar with situations that you're challenging a player taking a high ball off the wall. It's becoming more common to challenge these directly from the ceiling in order to conserve boost and match your height to the ball.

Remember, this pack is designed to teach you a defensive movement, don't try to score these starting out. Instead focus on positioning your car between the ball and your net and then taking a touch. Some shots like #8 will require you to stay high and close to the ceiling, while #9 forces you to descend quickly from the ceiling to make it to the ball.

Both of these situations require reaching the ceiling with speed and managing your boost efficiently to control your trajectory in the air. As a result, you'll be able to take these challenges quickly and confidently in game.

packs.notes:
Aimed at those of us that haven't really got the hang of dribbling yet.

First shot drops it on your roof moving forward slowly straight towards the goal. 1 second timer so you can't let it touch the floor.

Second shot has the ball rolling gently towards you for a chip into the dribble and straight towards goal.

Third shot has the ball rolling gently towards you but you need to turn the ball towards the goal before scoring.

Fourth shot is another drop onto the roof but again it needs turning towards the goal before scoring.

The pack is suitable for Gold ranked players who want to advance their offensive gameplay and become a more efficient striker.
packs.name: Offensive Essentials
packs.creator: Wayprotein
packs.notes:
I wanted to make a pack that was a shortcut to all the high level things I need to be practicing and warming up with. The shots include:
- 1 ball rolling towards you to pop up
- Setups on the right and left wall
- 1 bouncing power shot
- 1 controlled dribble
The setups are difficult, you should need to do some minor adjustment on each shot. I think every rank would benefit from using it, but the shots are going to be challenging until you're about GC level (depending on what you're trying to do with them).

packs.name: Verticals
packs.creator: Wayprotein
packs.notes:
***Note: The objective of these shots is NOT to score***

This pack is intended to teach new players the basics of fast aerials. for each shot, do the following:
1. Fast aerial directly upwards (a slight angle is okay)
2. Land on the ceiling and jump off.

Your flight path should be a clean line i.e. after you make contact with the ball, you shouldn't need much adjustment to hit the ceiling. If you can do that, you've completed the shot.

packs.staffComments: Work on your ball control and shooting accuracy with this pack that focuses on setting up the ball for a quick shot after two touches. Ideal for improving your offensive play and ensuring you can take advantage of shooting opportunities efficiently.
packs.name: 2 Touch Tap n' Shoot
packs.creator: Wayprotein
packs.notes:
Take a soft initial touch, then a shot on net. I suggest going through this in one of the following 2 methods:

1. Keep your first touch as close to you as possible and try to generate a large amount of power
2. Pop your first touch high in the air, and test how high you can go performing a dodge shot - see :08 seconds in the video for an example

One tip for success here is to make sure you're tapping boost right after your first touch to keep your car moving with the ball and to get setup to hit your shot with power.

packs.notes:
Great practice for realistic solo plays off the wall.

There are lots of training packs out there that will give you off the wall setups to practice your solo plays, but it can difficult to start translating that into game. This pack requires you to set the shot up yourself. This is the perfect way to master solo setups at speed end to end.

There are lots of times this comes up in Rocket League games, sometimes you just get a bad first touch on your wall play and end up awkwardly positioned. Sometimes you have to make a play on the ball and don't have much boost, this pack will help with all of the above. First touch is everything, so try to get a really controlled touch when taking the ball off the wall.

To add difficulty, try to take these as infield passes.

10 shot pack that simulates situations that you would commonly pass to a teammate in midfield. It's a great pack to throw go through occasionally to build some muscle memory around passing and some of the awkward car movements that the positions require.

packs.creator: EinsteinsLambda
packs.notes:
If you want to get shredded in the dribble gym then this is the pack for you. 

Shots 1-6 are basic ground dribbles sometimes I like to practice flicks and ground to air dribbles from these positions as well.

7-9 are rolling balls towards you. You can bounce dribble, go ground to air, or whatever.

10-12 are meant to be caught mid air and dribbled, however a lower ranked player can simply just catch the ball on top of their car and go for a dribble play.

13-36 are wall setups from just about everywhere on the pitch. Most are self setup. 29-32 are meant to be carries from your back wall. If you can't make it the whole way land and catch the ball on your car.

37-40 are inverted angle setups

packs.staffComments: A difficult mechanic to master, wavedash flicks can give you the edge you need in high-level gameplay. Great for those looking to add a bit of flair to their game or those aspiring for freestyle gameplay.

packs.creator: fieldz

packs.staffComments: This training pack is perfect for players looking to improve their wavedashing skills. Wavedashing is a technique that allows you to maintain your momentum after jumping, and it can be extremely useful for quick recoveries and fluid gameplay. These 20 shots will help you practice wavedashing in various scenarios, from simple straightaways to more complex angles and obstacles. Whether you're a Platinum player looking to level up, or just want to add another skill to your repertoire, this training pack is a must-try.
packs.name: Wavedash Training
packs.creator: Lazord
